From gary korenek Subject Re vs In article Michael Hamilton writes I have definitly seen a mother board with local bus slots which claimed to be able to support any CPU including the and Can someone throw some more informed light on this issue Michael Hamilton Some motherboards support VL bus and DX There is an option BIOS I think where additional wait s can be added with regard to CPU VL bus This slows the CPU down to a rate that gives the VL bus device s time to 'do their thing' These particular wait s are applied when the CPU transacts with VL bus device s You want to enable these wait s only if you are using a DX with VL bus This is from reading my motherboard manual and these are my interpre Your mileage may Strictly speaking VL and are not And there is at least one 'fudge' mechanism to physically allow it to Gary Korenek Network Management Technology Incorporated formerly Ferranti International Controls Sugar Land Texas